Package ch.nolix.tech.resource

Class Resource

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.nolix.core.bases.NamedElement
      • ch.nolix.tech.resource.Resource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Named

    public class Resource
extends NamedElement
    An resource is a piece of something that has a value. Of an resource, a certain amount can be possessed. An resource has a determined name. An resource can have super resources. An resource serves as any of its super resources. An resource is not mutable.
    Author:
    Silvan Wyss
